🚀 **Built a Mini Social Media Backend using Node.js**

Recently, I built a small backend project to strengthen my understanding of authentication, database relationships, and CRUD operations.

In this project, I implemented a **mini social-style system** where users can register, log in, create posts, like posts, and edit their content.

🔑 **Key Features**

• Secure **User Authentication** using JWT
• Password hashing with **bcrypt**
• **Protected routes** with custom middleware
• Create, edit, and update posts
• **Like / Unlike functionality**
• **User ↔ Posts relationship** using MongoDB references
• Fetching relational data using **Mongoose populate()**

🛠 **Tech Stack**

Node.js | Express.js | MongoDB | Mongoose | EJS | JWT | bcrypt

This project helped me understand how real backend systems manage **authentication, user sessions, and database relationships**.

